[2] Brazil (Rondonia)
Date: Fri 4 Dec 2009
Source: Rondonia Dinamica [in Portuguese, trans. & summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://rondoniadinamica.com/ler.php?id=11467&edi=1&sub=4>


From the beginning of this year [2009] up to the 1st days of
December 2009, more than 1450 cases of [dengue] disease have been
reported. "We are reporting nearly 150 cases of the disease per
month, and this is worrying," said the chief of endemics in Cacoal,
Flaviano Melo Flaviano. According to Flaviano, Health is not the only
[unit] to advance the combat against the dengue mosquito; the
community also needs to play its part as well as the public and
private sectors, which must unite their actions to reduce the
incidence in the municipality.

The rate of people infected with dengue in Cacoal is daunting,
requiring an urgent solution to the problem, says the president of
the Cacoal City Council, Luiz Carlos Katatal, who believes that a
meeting with the environmental authorities, police, health, schools,
universities, society, and the media can be organized for urgent
action to raise awareness in the community.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed-port@promedmail.org>

[The 7 Dec 2009 edition of So Noticias (in Portuguese)
<http://www.sonoticias.com.br/noticias/11/97490/sob-risco-de-epidemia-alta-floresta-pede-fumace-para-conter-dengue/>
reported that there were 65 dengue cases in October and 132 in
November, and for all of 2009 to date a total of 325 recorded dengue cases.

An interactive map of the Cacoal region of Rondonia state can be
accessed at <http://www.maplandia.com/brazil/rondonia/cacoal/> and a
map showing the location of Alta Floresta at
<http://www.maplandia.com/brazil/rondonia/alta-floresta/>. - Mod.TY]

