[3] Brazil (Mato Grosso)
Date: Fri 4 Dec 2009
Source: Expresso MT, Gazeta Digital report [in Portuguese, trans. &
summ. Mod.TY, edited]
<http://www.expressomt.com.br/noticiaBusca.asp?cod=49471&codDep=3>


DHF has killed 2 people in Caceres (225 km [140 mi] west of Cuiaba),
bringing to 5 the number of deaths in the city in a month.

In Mato Grosso, there are now 48 fatalities from [dengue] disease. Of
the 1912 new [dengue] cases recorded in the past week [week of 28 Nov
2009], 186 are residents of Caceres. The city has had a decline in
the [_Aedes aegypti_] household infestation rate from 3.5 to 2.4,
according to municipal Epidemiological Surveillance, but the number
of ill people has not stopped growing.

The Ministry of Health placed Caceres among the 10 municipalities in
Brazil with risk of a dengue outbreak, after a rapid survey index of
_Aedes aegypti_ this year [2009], noting that 4.7 percent of the
buildings of the city have larvae of the mosquito vector of the
disease [virus]. The number is higher than considered ideal, [which
is] less than one percent.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-PORT
<promed-port@promedmail.org>

[The 7 Dec 2009 edition of O Documento (in Portuguese)
<http://www.odocumento.com.br/materia.php?id=316331> reported that
the Secretariat of Health of Cuiaba indicated that the _Aedes
aegypti_ household index increased to over 3.9 percent, the worst
level of 2009. The number of recorded dengue cases in the city
increased from 688 in October to 4878 in November 2009, with a total
of 5179 for all of 2009.

An interactive map showing the locations of Caceres and Cuiaba in
Mato Grosso state, Brazil, can be accessed at
<http://www.maplandia.com/brazil/mato-grosso/caceres/>. - Mod.TY]

