[4] India (Delhi)
Date: Wed 2 Dec 2009
Source: The Times of India (TOI), Indo Asian News Service (IANS)
report [edited]
<http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/One-more-dengue-death-take=s-Delhi-toll-to-3/articleshow/5292446.cms>


A 45-year-old man has died of dengue in the capital, taking the toll
due to the mosquito borne disease to 3 in the city, the health
department said on Wednesday [2 Dec 2009].

"The man, a resident of Karawal Nagar in east Delhi, was admitted to
St Stephen's Hospital on 21 Nov [2009] and was diagnosed to be
suffering from dengue. He died 30 Nov 2009. His death due to dengue
was confirmed today [Wed 2 Dec 2009]. With this, the official toll in
Delhi is 3," Debashish Bhattacharya, state nodal officer for dengue
cases, told IANS.

With 12 new dengue cases reported on Wednesday [2 Dec 2009], the
tally of those affected by the disease crossed the 1100 mark. "There
were 12 new cases reported on Wednesday. The cumulative total number
of cases is 1106 now," the official added.

Earlier, 2 people died of dengue in Delhi, a 15-year-old boy and a
9-year-old boy.

With the onset of winter, the health department is hoping that the
number of dengue cases will drop, since the breeding of the carrier
mosquito cannot occur below 15 deg C [59 deg F].

Last year [2008], the national capital reported 2 dengue deaths and a
total of 1312 cases.

