[5] Taiwan
Date: Mon 7 Dec 2009
Source: Sina [in Chinese, machine trans., summ., edited]
<http://news.sina.com.cn/c/2009-12-07/191516732296s.shtml>


Warm winters thus far in southern Taiwan have brought a dengue fever
epidemic, the Taiwan authorities of the Health Department report. An
official command center was set up for the dengue fever epidemic. So
far this year [2009] there have been 648 local cases with 2 deaths.
The epidemic will be the most severe test next year [2010].

According to a Taiwan's Central News Agency report, the Taiwan
authorities of the Department of Health, Deputy Secretary for Disease
Control, Zhou Zhihao said today [7 Dec 2009] that this year's [2009]
local [dengue] fever is concentrated in Kaohsiung City and Pingtung
County, namely, Kaohsiung City 438 cases, Kaohsiung County 81 cases
and 64 cases in Pingtung County. Because since the beginning of
winter in southern Taiwan the high temperature has not decreased, the
epidemic remains high.

Health director Chih-Liang Yaung predicted that this wave of dengue
fever will spread to the next year [2010], forming the acid test for
the eradication of the vector mosquito. Spraying alone will lead to
emergence of mosquitoes resistant to disease prevention measures so
control must be accomplished with other measures.

